it all went down, and what might come next=E2=80=A6

* Tony=E2=80=99s turnaround: Gonzales was perhaps the best-prepared incumbe=
nt this cycle, having honed his campaigning and fundraising
chops back when this was a competitive seat, before 2021 redistricting. Gon=
zales ran like his career depended on it, and rightly so: The state=E2=80=
=99s Republican apparatus was mostly aligned against him. Over the last few=
 years, he has infuriated the right, particularly for being the lone Texas =
House Republican to vote for a 2022 gun control bill in the aftermath of th=
e Uvalde school shooting, which happened in his district.

One of the most striking items in the Herrera opposition research file was =
