For now, no major Republican outside groups have purchased TV time in the L=
aredo or San Antonio media markets. If the G.O.P. doesn=E2=80=99t make a se=
rious play here in the fall, it would seem logical that recruiting a top-sh=
elf candidate in Laredo will be a top priority for the N.R.C.C. next year.

