          <td style=3D"padding-bottom: 36px; color: #000000; font-size: 16p=
x; line-height: 30px; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0;"><b><i>Tina Nguyen</=
i>:</b> <b>Let=E2=80=99s start with an easy, non-controversial topic. Voter=
s have overwhelmingly turned out to enshrine abortion access in their state=
 constitutions, and often cite a candidate=E2=80=99s position on the topic =
as a deciding factor in the voting booth. The issue will be on the ballots =
in swing states like Colorado and Florida in November. What do you make of =
the backlash to <i>Dobbs</i>?</b><br/><br/><i>Ralph Reed</i>: On the 40th a=
nniversary of <i>Roe</i>, <i>Time </i>magazine had that famous cover where =
they said the feminists won a historic victory with <i>Roe v. Wade</i>. The=
 sub headline was =E2=80=9C... and they=E2=80=99ve been losing ever since=
=E2=80=9D=E2=80=94which was true. From the time of <i>Roe</i> until <i>Dobb=
s</i>, the feminists in the pro-abortion lobby did nothing <i>but</i> lose.=
 And we began our long march through the institutions,
through the courts, through Congress, through the presidency, and through s=
tate legislatures, and systematically restricted abortion and protected inn=
ocent human life. My greatest concern is that 40 years from now, somebody=
=E2=80=99s going to write a headline like that about us: that <i>Dobbs</i> =
was the greatest victory in the history of our movement=E2=80=94and then af=
ter that, all we did was lose. And so the question is, what do we do about =
that? <br/><br/>I think the answer is that we respond in the post-<i>Dobbs<=
/i> environment exactly the way we did in the post-<i>Roe</i> environment, =
in the sense that it=E2=80=99s all about state legislative action. The Demo=
crats are the real extremists here=E2=80=94and <b>Joe Biden</b> is the real=
 extremist=E2=80=94because they=E2=80=99re for abortion on demand. You can =
debate when [life begins], but for all practical purposes, [they claim that=
 it=E2=80=99s] at any stage of pregnancy, and they want to pay for it with =
tax dollars=E2=80=94which means repealing the Hyde Amendment,
which Joe Biden supported for 42 years. If you do the polling on this, by t=
he way, the majority of the American people are fine with restrictions, at =
the absolute latest, after the first trimester. <br/><br/>I guess it was in=
<b> Hillary</b>=E2=80=99s interview with <i>The New York Times</i> that cre=
ated so much buzz, in which she said, =E2=80=9COur formula was always safe,=
 legal, and rare.=E2=80=9D Remember, <i>Roe</i> was based on a trimester sy=
stem, and the argument was that after the first trimester, it was going to =
be possible to restrict, and therefore it would be very rare. And it would =
be legal, and therefore safe. And she said that her campaign advisors told =
her, =E2=80=9CYou can=E2=80=99t say =E2=80=98rare=E2=80=99 anymore.=E2=80=
=9D That=E2=80=99s when the party transitioned to on-demand, making it paid=
 for under Medicaid. It=E2=80=99s treated as if it=E2=80=99s a positive goo=
d. <br/><br/>Elective abortions paid for under Medicaid, which the Alan Gut=
tmacher Institute, Planned Parenthood=E2=80=99s research arm, has estimated=
 to have led
to as many as 300,000 additional abortions a year=E2=80=94if you do the pol=
ling on this, our position is a winning position. It=E2=80=99s where the ma=
jority of the American people are. They don=E2=80=99t want unlimited aborti=
on, and they don=E2=80=99t want to pay for [it with] tax dollars. The probl=
em is that in a campaign environment, that=E2=80=99s doing us very little g=
ood, because they=E2=80=99re able to run these ads saying, =E2=80=9CSo and =
so is for a federal ban on abortion.=E2=80=9D And after that, you=E2=80=99r=
e explaining, and when you=E2=80=99re explaining, you=E2=80=99re losing.<br=
/><br/>We just have to plow through this current environment. President Tru=
mp, who will be the nominee, is going to emphasize state legislative action=
=2E We should emphasize state legislati=
ve action. And neither the pro-choice=20=
nor the pro-abortion side is going to be able to pass any sweeping federal =
legislation anyway.<br/><br/>The pro-abortion movement is enjoying a short-=
term sugar high with these initiative and referendum victories, but eventua=
lly
those will come to an end. Because there=E2=80=99s a limit to the number of=
